[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering Plexus component options**\n\nI’m evaluating whether to use the Plexus container component discovery, which requires dynamic class loading. I want to avoid uncertainty and ensure we have compile guarantees. Examining exceptions like TransferFailedException and ResourceDoesNotExistException sounds necessary. About naming, can I use Wagon_ssh_externalTest? It fits as a top-level public class. I should also check for any deprecated APIs, but it seems ScpExternalWagon is fine. I need to ensure compatibility with assertj and be cautious with `Files.setPosixFilePermissions` on non-posix systems.\n\n**Handling shell single quote escapes**\n\nI’m working on how to properly escape single quotes in the shell. The escape function I’m considering looks like `return \"'\" + value.replace(\"'\", \"'\\\"'\\\"'\") + \"'\";`. I think this should work smoothly, but I’m wondering if I need a lambda here. It seems like I can proceed without it for this implementation. I want to ensure that everything functions correctly without adding unnecessary complexity. That's my focus right now!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0728ac310b247ca7016a03ae4c2ac081939418c65f1dc1fbdf\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqA65hzL15y-xe8U9NtzBqEJcFF72Dx3e_0vO00dHVKcVeNIWwqZgZfSDlRWU5ALZKKDeenKVKz-qP_Q9YV932627jwVUn3a0SsglYYy255bIAo65Z8Cyy7Z6H2v7jHnxzcjw2ryhslHIftEMy-m8VSohJDyEd3-h4Wci7KQh-qHIGZe90vS1tAw9DbuQBcrMXaDU3ciI9ViZV6wA3M1UrF-VuQdAmiaAEKla0hVXk_7Hap8IL_k3JDXIF-LOBCmGbBAxzK6kKHRYHHXOs8T-F6D4uYVHlj1lHPsUrvgct-lMZuvxtvEgJVDILe7-gqjHExAgUrxrUAEHN6y519THQ9fl6o3wdm7WP4UcKGVAYQYEvIelaft9cFc3P4Pj9a7UjSdP2A0N4cwdLP8V34e9F5_cInDQXuU8TBVGQAR7_rX1Ji--qhixDY49FKdv8stWT3xq5Ryt7RD0iZphBR1Tfc_EBms3X8JZAXqxPSO7bOIj8v6GolrLAnenZr2Rsa0g7gjKYX_UOteHmuFcZdaUPqma86tr4m7OqH7iZb3Ake8LFWsBj8Kii1bHkAM42vGZ7dssLz35HpsNJGeuwARxftYvZSqn2xznFcYvkoAfoV3oXP5jqIZLarjt1LFEyMKcjd-FfanreJv1f